  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing emergency health and nutrition services to drought affected communities in Somalia (IRF)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The consortium will provide emergency health and nutrition services to drought affected communities in 69 districts across 18 regions of Somalia/Somaliland. The project will build on current interventions in SNS and CHANGE, as well as scale up to new locations to ensure maximum coverage. The health component will provide treatment of common endemic conditions including the main causes of child mortality i.e. diarrhoea, pneumonia and malaria. The nutrition component will entail community mobilization and screening for cases of acute malnutrition; referral of acute malnutrition cases; treatment of severe and moderately acute malnutrition cases; prevention of malnutrition through IYCF promotion and support and health education; and nutrition surveillance and monitoring.</narrative>
  </description>
